pullRequest.title: [ML] adding prediction_field_type to inference config
pullRequest.bodyText:
Data frame analytics dynamically determines the classification field type. This field type then dictates the encoded JSON that is written to Elasticsearch.
Inference needs to know about this field type so that it may provide the EXACT SAME predicted values as analytics.
Here is added a new field prediction_field_type which indicates the desired type. Options are: string (DEFAULT), number, boolean (where close_to(1.0) == true, false otherwise).
Analytics provides the default prediction_field_type when the model is created from the process.

nodes.bodyText: Could fromString and toString methods be next to each other so that it's easier to examine whether they are compatible?
IMO switch(this) would result in more readable code here.
Can it be the case the value is greater than 1.0?
Is it possible to unify and use predictedFieldType or predictionFieldType throughout the codebase?

One suggestion that would help keeping the strings "string", "int", "bool" in one class would be as follows:

Make Classification.getPredictionFieldType method return the new PredictedFieldType enum.
Here (i.e. in AnalyticsResultProcessor) remove the translation in lines 277-285 (maybe keep the null -> STRING translation)
There (i.e. in Classification) in getParams method translate the enum to appropriate string ("string", "int", "bool").

prediction_field_type
